// util/m_random.bet — DOOM's demo-critical RNG (m_random.c). The RNG state (prndindex,
// rndindex) lives in gs.TickState; the 256-byte rndtable is a slab in TickState populated by
// initRndtable (the verbatim literal below, copied from m_random.c). P_Random is the
// deterministic one used by the play sim — it MUST reproduce m_random.c exactly:
// prndindex = (prndindex+1)&0xff; return rndtable[prndindex]. Do NOT use math.cook.
// This is verified bit-for-bit by ports/doom/goldens/random.golden (via the goldens.bet twin).
pull "../defs/gs" as gs

// initRndtable: fill a 256-slot []u8 with id's rndtable literal. Value-threaded (slabs are
// value-copied by the interpreter): call as `g.tick.rndtable = m_random.initRndtable(g.tick.rndtable)`.
